</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1435,151,378]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,302,191,217]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Habitat.</emphasis>
Beneath rotting grass lying on red soil at the edeg of one of the native gardens (
<bibRefCitation author="Loveridge" firstAuthor="Loveridge" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" pagination="209 - 337" refId="ref60644" refString="Loveridge, A. (1936) Scientific results of an expedition to rain forest regions in eastern Africa. V. Reptiles. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology at Harvard College (Cambridge), 79 (5), 209 - 337, Pls. 1 - 9." type="journal article" year="1936">Loveridge, 1936</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
